        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2019-09-26 14:15:51.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\n> Patch Set 1:\n> \n> Please use the centos docker node instead of ubuntu\n\nAll our build and test jobs are on the ubuntu node. Why would the release job not be on a consistent node with the rest of VVP jobs?",
        "patchset_number": 1
      },
      {
        "id": "a6474238e3eac07d9a64d17f41603773285d0533",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 481,
          "name": "Jessica Wagantall",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "jwagantall@linuxfoundation.org",
          "username": "jwagantall"
        },
        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2019-09-26 14:36:23.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nThis is because we run SIGUL commands to sign the tag that goes into the repo. \nSIGUL is only available in centos for now. Other than that, all release operations are mostly using lftools for maven releases and docker for container releases.",
        "patchset_number": 1
      },
